---
import StarlightPage from '@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro';
---

<StarlightPage
	frontmatter={{
		title: 'Cookie policy',
		description: 'What cookies the docs site sets, what is collected, and how to withdraw consent.',
		tableOfContents: false,
	}}
	hasSidebar={false}
>
	<p>
		We use a single analytics tool, PostHog, to see which docs pages visitors
		read and how they move through the site. No advertising cookies, no
		cross-site tracking, no profiling, no data sold. If you decline, no
		analytics cookies are set and no events are sent.
	</p>

	<h2>What we store</h2>
	<p>
		When you click <strong>Accept</strong>, PostHog sets a first-party cookie
		and a localStorage entry on <code>gaffer.kurrent.io</code>. They hold an
		anonymous identifier so PostHog can tell repeat page views apart from new
		ones. The identifier is not linked to your name or email.
	</p>
	<p>
		We also store a small <code>gaffer-docs:cookie-consent</code> entry in
		localStorage with the value <code>accepted</code> or <code>declined</code>
		so you don't see the banner on every page. This is set regardless of which
		option you choose — it is the record of your choice.
	</p>

	<h2>What gets sent</h2>
	<ul>
		<li>Page URL, referrer, viewport, browser and OS (from the user agent).</li>
		<li>
			Coarse geolocation (country, region) inferred from your IP by PostHog at
			ingest time. The raw IP is then discarded.
		</li>
	</ul>
	<p>
		Data is sent to PostHog's EU ingest (<code>eu.i.posthog.com</code>) and
		stored in the EU. We do not run session replay, heatmaps, autocapture, or
		any third-party advertising or marketing pixels.
	</p>

	<h2>Global Privacy Control</h2>
	<p>
		If your browser sends a
		<a href="https://globalprivacycontrol.org/">Global Privacy Control</a>
		signal, we treat it as a decline automatically: the banner is never shown
		and PostHog is never loaded. You don't need to do anything.
	</p>

	<h2 id="withdraw">Changing your mind</h2>
	<p>
		If you previously accepted, the button below tells PostHog to stop
		capturing, forget the anonymous identifier it stored, and reloads the page
		so nothing further is sent.
	</p>
	<p>
		<button type="button" class="withdraw-btn" id="withdraw-consent">Withdraw consent</button>
		<span class="withdraw-status" id="withdraw-status" hidden></span>
	</p>

	<h2>Contact</h2>
	<p>
		Questions about this policy:
		<a href="mailto:privacy@kurrent.io">privacy@kurrent.io</a>. For broader
		data-handling questions, see the <a href="/privacy/">privacy policy</a>.
	</p>
</StarlightPage>

<script is:inline>
	(function () {
		const btn = document.getElementById('withdraw-consent');
		const status = document.getElementById('withdraw-status');
		if (!btn || !status) return;

		const CONSENT_KEY = 'gaffer-docs:cookie-consent';

		function setStatus(text) {
			status.textContent = text;
			status.hidden = false;
		}

		// Reflect the current state on load so the button copy matches what
		// it'll actually do.
		try {
			const current = localStorage.getItem(CONSENT_KEY);
			if (current !== 'accepted') {
				btn.textContent = 'Consent already withdrawn';
				btn.disabled = true;
				setStatus(
					current === 'declined'
						? 'You previously declined analytics on this site.'
						: "Analytics is off — you haven't accepted yet.",
				);
			}
		} catch (e) {
			/* private mode - leave the button in its default state */
		}

		// Best-effort removal of PostHog's stored identifiers. Covers the case
		// where PostHog never loaded (ad blocker / CSP / offline) but left
		// cookies and localStorage from an earlier accepted session, so the
		// withdraw button can't rely on the live SDK to clean up after itself.
		function clearPostHogStorage() {
			try {
				for (const key of Object.keys(localStorage)) {
					if (key.startsWith('ph_') || key.includes('posthog')) localStorage.removeItem(key);
				}
			} catch (e) {}
			try {
				for (const cookie of document.cookie.split(';')) {
					const name = cookie.split('=')[0].trim();
					if (name.startsWith('ph_') || name.includes('posthog')) {
						document.cookie = `${name}=; Max-Age=0; path=/`;
					}
				}
			} catch (e) {}
		}

		btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
			// Tell the live posthog instance (if loaded) to stop and clear its
			// persisted state, then sweep up any leftover identifiers in case
			// the SDK wasn't loaded to do it itself.
			try {
				window.posthog?.opt_out_capturing?.();
				window.posthog?.reset?.();
			} catch (e) {
				/* keep going - we still want to update our own consent record */
			}
			clearPostHogStorage();
			try {
				localStorage.setItem(CONSENT_KEY, 'declined');
			} catch (e) {}
			btn.disabled = true;
			setStatus('Done. Reloading to finish clearing analytics…');
			setTimeout(() => window.location.reload(), 700);
		});
	})();
</script>

<style>
	.withdraw-btn {
		appearance: none;
		background: var(--color-accent);
		color: var(--palette-white);
		border: 1px solid var(--color-accent);
		border-radius: 6px;
		padding: 0.55rem 1rem;
		font: inherit;
		font-weight: 500;
		cursor: pointer;
	}
	.withdraw-btn:hover:not(:disabled) {
		background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-accent) 85%, white);
	}
	.withdraw-btn:disabled {
		background: transparent;
		color: var(--color-muted);
		border-color: var(--color-shade-50);
		cursor: default;
	}
	.withdraw-status {
		margin-inline-start: 0.75rem;
		font-size: var(--sl-text-sm);
		color: var(--color-muted);
	}
</style>
